description:
&lt;p&gt;The London Medical Imaging and AI Centre for Value-Based Healthcare&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a highly collaborative, cross-institutional Centre of Excellence pooling worldwide expertise in artificial intelligence (AI), healthcare, and data from leaders in the industry, research, and clinical practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AI Centre develops new diagnostic and treatment solutions across targeted disease pathways to generate solutions that improve patient outcomes and reduce costs, driving health and economic benefit in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More information about our work and our partners can be found on the AI Centre website&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To illustrate the breadth of the opportunity provided by AI, we are targeting diverse clinical pathways, from head to toe, in early life and old age. Each pathway is typically allocated a tri-partite project team comprising membership from academia, healthcare, and industry. Together, each project team is co-developing a specific AI solution to demonstrate clinical benefit to patients with an AI prototype.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This clinical pathways transformation work is headed by the AI Transformation Lead, whom this post-holder will report to and it is supported also by several team members within the core AI Centre delivery team. Team members work as part of a cross-organisational multi-functional team, including clinical and health care professionals, as well as programme and business management functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AI Project Manager will work across multiple projects within the AI Centre, ensuring that the project priorities are identified and aligned; plans are developed and monitored, resolving/mitigating any risks and issues, or escalating to the relevant Boards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will provide key leadership and expertise in project management and delivery for the AI Centre, including progress reporting, risk and issue management, assurance, and developing and maintaining the team’s project or programme scope, PID and plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a significant scope to expand the role to align with the post-holders experience and interests, including getting involved in work that is already underway involving developing policy, publishing best practice, and AI evaluation .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this vacancy will close on the 11th November at midnight&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHaris ShuaibEmail addressharis.shuaib@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
